CatDescriptText: Mr. Nathaniel Armstead, '61 high school graduate, Homewood, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in the Pittsburgh Courier Newspaper, September 9, 1961, pg. 5 with question: "Do you think that in the final analysis, the uncommitted darker nations will join the democratic (pro-Western) or Communistic bloc?  Why?" answer reads: "I believe they will join the Western bloc, because they believe in democracy the same as we Americans believe in it."
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Portrait of man wearing eyeglasses and light colored short sleeve shirt; Portrait of Nathaniel Armstead wearing light colored button down collared shirt with short sleeves, standing in front of wall with carved cornice and scroll
